<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The latest round of stalled U.N.-mediated Persian Gulf peace talks in Geneva 
between Iran and Iraq ended without any progress or a firm date for their 
resumption, U.N. Secretary General Javier Perez de Cuellar reported. He said 
his special representative, Sweden's U.N. ambassador, Jan Eliasson, will be in 
touch with both sides in New York to "prepare for a possible meting in June." 
The two sides blame each other for the continuing deadlock over the issue of 
withdrawing troops to recognized borders. The two sides disagree over where the 
border lies. Fighting stopped when a cease-fire went into effect last Aug. 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
