<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Islamic militants in Sudan attacked a Roman Catholic center for the destitute 
and dying, injuring a nun and three other people, a Khartoum newspaper 
reported. The newspaper Sudani said the Muslims left a mosque Friday after a 
clergyman criticized the presence of the church-run relief center and attacked 
the hospice in Omdurman, twin city of Khartoum. It said the militants reacted 
after the government refused to impose strict Islamic sharia law on the 
country. The next day, the paper said, a group of Christians retaliated with an 
arson attack against mosque. 
</P>
</TEXT>
