<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Record cold air chilled the Northeast and Great Lakes, with the mercury 
plunging below freezing, but temperatures soared into the 90s as a stretch of 
summer weather lingered over the plains. Unseasonably cold temperatures 
stretched from New Jersey to Michigan, the National Weather Service said. 
Cities setting or tying record daily lows included Alpena, Mich., (18); 
Atlantic City, N.J., (24); Erie, Pa., (27); Hartford, Conn., (26), and 
Rochester, N.Y., (24). Meanwhile, among the record highs set or tied: Amarillo, 
Tex., (93); Denver (82) and Midland, Tex., (96). 
</P>
