<TEXT>
<P>
A fire killed at least 19 people Sunday in an illegal Taiwan video theater, the 
flames blocking the only escape route and trapping customers in tiny viewing 
booths, state-run radio said. 
</P>
<P>
The blaze quickly engulfed the maze-like theater in Chungli, northern Taiwan, 
where patrons were watching videotaped films in private plywood cubicles. Video 
theaters, where customers select their own videotapes of pirated U.S. movies 
for viewing in cubicles, are common in Taiwan. 
