<P>
JOINT DIABETES STUDY PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soviet and U.S. doctors announced a joint research project aimed at finding 
ways to treat diabetes, which affects the body's ability to regulate blood 
sugar levels. 
</P>
<P>
"What we are doing will be a collaborative effort that will involve faculty 
exchanges, joint clinical research efforts and the development of special 
diabetes clinical care," said William Henry, senior vice president of the 
International Diabetes Center in Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
The doctors announced the cooperative project after a weeklong visit by a team 
of Soviet doctors. 
</P>
<P>
A group of American physicians will go to the Soviet Central Institute for 
Advanced Medical Studies in Moscow in January to teach doctors there about U.S. 
efforts to fight the potentially fatal disease. 
</P>
