MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Claudia Puig and ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The 
Times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A.C. Nielsen Co. is inches from beating out Arbitron Ratings Co. for a more 
than $30-million, multiyear contract to upgrade TV ratings measurement of 
Latino households for the all-Spanish Univision and Telemundo networks. "It 
will probably be Nielsen, but no contract has been signed," said Doug Darfield, 
vice president of research for Univision. "You can agree in principle, but once 
you start poring over contract documents, many things can happen. It's in the 
hands of the lawyers." When and if negotiations are finalized, he said, Nielsen 
will install People Meters in about 1,000 Latino households in Los Angeles and 
other cities nationwide. The new service won't be fully operational until 1991. 
Claudia Puig and ALEENE MacMINN 
