<P>
CONTINENTAL AIRLINES CUTS SUMMER FARES FOR CHILDREN TO AS LOW AS $1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Continental Airlines dropped summer children's air fares today to as low as $1 
round trip, reductions the carrier said could save families up to 55% on their 
total summer air travel. 
</P>
<P>
"We've rewritten the book on children's summer air fares today," said 
Continental spokesman David Messing. "Summer is the time of year when everyone 
plans a big vacation trip with the kids. For a typical family with two kids, 
each of those kids can now travel for as low as $1." 
</P>
<P>
A limited number of the reduced fares are available for purchase now through 
May 26 for travel June 1 through Sept. 10. They can be purchased for children 
ages 2 to 17 when traveling with an adult who has bought a Continental MaxSaver 
ticket, the airline said. 
</P>
<P>
The special fares are non-refundable, although Continental said families will 
be allowed to change reservations once at no charge if the destination remains 
the same and appropriate discount seats are available. 
</P>
