<P>
NBC WILL AIR PGA SENIORS TOURNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NBC Sports, attracted by the additions of "rookies" Jack Nicklaus and Lee 
Trevino, announced today a multiyear agreement to televise the PGA Seniors 
Championship beginning next year. 
</P>
<P>
The PGA Seniors Championship, founded in 1937 at Augusta National Golf Club 
with the support of Bobby Jones, is the oldest tournament in senior golf by 
more than 40 years. 
</P>
<P>
Trevino turns 50 Dec. 1 and Nicklaus follows Jan. 21, 1990, making both 
eligible for seniors competition. 
</P>
<P>
NBC Sports President Arthur Watson confirmed that the likelihood of Nicklaus 
and Trevino joining the field influenced the network's decision. 
</P>
<P>
"Very much so," he said. 
</P>
